name: Pura Kahyangan Jagat Bukit Dharma Durga Kutri
address: F863+W3V, Jl. Raya Buruan, Buruan, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1:
Pura Kahyangan Jagat  "Bukit Darma Durga Kutri"
Feeling grateful for worshiping in such historic place üòá. Need a sturdy feet to step on hundred steps to access main temple area.
review 2: Nicely empty when I was there, end of January, no fees, no sarong-sentinels... Climb the stairs towards the inner sanctuary on a rock, turning around halfway you can see mountains in the distance...
review 3: Beautiful Durga Pura with a large ancient Durga murti at the top of the temple.
review 4:
AD 930.
Open upon request to the local caretaker.
Please respect the place.
review 5: Pura Kahyangan Jagat Bukit Dharma Durga Kutri is very magical, it gives you a very peaceful feeling and drag you back to the ancient time.

name: Babi Guling Ibu Desak
address: Jl. Raya Semebaung No.120x, Bedulu, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: Food is yummy and service is very good. Very nice option to eat as the locals do. I may have chosen a bad spot to sit because the smoke from the pig cooking blew in from the wind and made my eyes water shut, but the servers were very kind and helped me move to a new table away from the smoke! A must-visit for sure.
review 2: Pork tasted very weird and was super chewy and had lots flies around, seems like they cover it in lots of spicy sauce to hide the taste, maybe a great place for locals but wouldn't recomemd for tourist that don't want to get sick.
review 3: Food is ok...lawar Bali and main Dish Babi Guling was tasty...but the extra Kulit wasn't crunchy and that was a Minus....the Price is ok and the Service too
review 4:
Very decent authentic babi guling for very reasonable price! This babi guling special is only 30k, with good quantity.
Close from Tegal Linggah Cliff Temple.
review 5: Lovely and very cheap. Don't be afraid about the "aspect" because the food is tasty. It's a so-local restaurant. Simple and small.

review 1: This place is amazing, the food was delious and the price was very reasonable
review 2:
Ordered take away here yesterday. Nasi goreng, fuyonghai, capcoy and ayam.goreng. the nasi goreng was not good
I think they used old oil on that one. Ayam goreng was to salty. Other two dishes were good en fresh
review 3: Selling chinese food with cheap price and delicious taste. Recommended for budget travellers and those who seeks halal cuisine in bali
review 4: Good menu and fair price, try it then you will taste this good Warung
review 5: Cheap local foods open until 10 pm. Cheap but delicious. I will try all the food if I have the chance.
